Windows os stores hashed user account passwords locally in the SAM.
Hashing the process of converting a piece of data into another value/
windows versions upto windows server 2003 utilize two different types of hashes 
>LM
>NTLM --> v1,v2
Elevated priviliges are required in order to access and intract with the LSASS Process
Modern version of Windows the sam database encrypted with syskey.

LM is default hash algorithm in winos 
password is broken into two seven-charachter chunks.
All charcters are converted into upercase
each chunk is hashed seperately with DES algorithm.

NTLM is collection of auth protocols that are utilized in windows to facilitate auth between computers.
it needs a valid username and passwords
Does not split the hash into two chunks
Case sensitive
Allows the use of symbols and unicode charcters. hashed with md4

